<subSubSection id="9E3BB2E21BA2FD7B09B0B27BF89A8523" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="52B32E7A3A117FF8BEA7FEE483913826" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="48B131D623252626C29026F09C377902" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
<taxonomicName id="87958B31196287666205417462F09B5A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Scabiosa" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Scabiosa balcanica" order="Dipsacales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="balcanica">
<emphasis id="C92A8175D9359C379623A8EE19E1560E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Scabiosa balcanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a range-restricted Balkan endemic species distributed in Greece, Bulgaria, North Macedonia and Serbia (
<bibRefCitation id="85534652125718908577C367211991A4" author="Petrova, A." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="293 - 311" refId="B7669158" refString="Petrova, A., Vladimirov, V., 2010. Balkan endemics in the Bulgarian flora. Phytologia Balcanica 16 (2): 293 - 311" title="Balkan endemics in the Bulgarian flora" volume="16" year="2010">Petrova and Vladimirov 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="F596FCA4349EDE64E68DF0FE669B67F4" author="Dimopoulos, P." journalOrPublisher="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668013" refString="Dimopoulos, P., Raus, T., Bergmeier, E., Constantinidis, T., Iatrou, G., Kokkini, S., Strid, A., D.Tzanoudakis, , 2013. Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist. Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" title="Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist" year="2013">Dimopoulos et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="0D8A38265F5859B504C324E23754EF18" author="Tomovic, G." journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="173 - 202" refId="B7670093" refString="Tomovic, G., Niketic, M., Lakusic, D., Ranđelovic, V., Stevanovic, V., 2014. Balkan endemic plants in Central Serbia and Kosovo regions: distribution patterns, ecological characteristics and centres of diversity. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 176: 173 - 202" title="Balkan endemic plants in Central Serbia and Kosovo regions: distribution patterns, ecological characteristics and centres of diversity" volume="176" year="2014">
<normalizedToken id="F2A0C39EEE1FB46185496E30202C0747" originalValue="Tomović">Tomovic</normalizedToken>
et al. 2014
</bibRefCitation>
). The only report from the Greek floristic region of the NE seems to be on Mt. Falakro (
<bibRefCitation id="708584EE88A080305E393A4087056EB8" author="Kokkini, S." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668846" refString="Kokkini, S., 1991. Mountain Flora of Greece 2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Mountain Flora of Greece 2" year="1991">Kokkini 1991</bibRefCitation>
). This is the second population discovered in the NE region of Greece.
</paragraph>
